<p class="govuk-body">
I have considered the EVIDENTIAL STAGE. My findings are as follows:
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
This is a supported Domestic Violence Case against the victim Marge Simpson. On THURSDAY 30TH JANUARY 2025, the defendants and victim have been in her home address when the defendant has been accused the victim of cheating on him. The victim has denied this which has angered the defendant and caused him to stand up, tense up and shout "LEAVE MY FUCKING HOUSE". The defendant has then clenched his right fist, raised it and said if she did not leave then he would punch her. He has then made more threats including “I WILL SKULL DRAG YOU OUT OF THE ADDRESS” causing the victim to fear for her immediate and unlawful violence. The defendant himself left the address and the Police have been called.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
Bart Simpson also slapped his mother to the left hand side of the face.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
Police have attended the address and the victim stated over the last 2 years the defendant has accused her of cheating, demanding to know who she was with, wanting to know where she is, who she is with and stating she was unfaithful. The defendant demands access to the victims phone, goes through her phone and feels that she is being “controlled” by him. She feels if she does not do as told, then he will become angry and volatile.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">The victim has provided a statement to Police.</p>
<p class="govuk-body">She has requested a Restraining Order.</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
I then considered the ANTICIPATED PLEA. Please find details and rationale as follows; the defendant was interviewed on FRIDAY 31ST JANUARY 2025 at CENTRAL PERK POLICE CUSTODY. The defendant was interviewed by PC MURRAY and denied both offences. Regarding the Common Assault, the defendant stated that the victim assaulted him.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
I can confirm the OIC has explored all reasonable lines of enquiry.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
I considered the PUBLIC INTEREST STAGE. My findings are as follows:
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
This is a High Risk Domestic Incident between the victim and the defendant. The victim is terrified of the defendant but has been brave enough to provide a statement to the Police and is supporting a Police Prosecution.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
Further to this, there has been a 37% increase in violence against women or girls between 2018–2023. In 2023 alone, over 1 million crimes against women and girls were recorded in England and Wales which makes up 20% of crimes recorded by Police.
